result.execSummary:
The defendant Vicki L. Dobratz was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possession of THC (2nd+ Offense), a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(3g)(e).
  • Bail Jumping-Misdemeanor, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.49(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Vicki L. Dobratz in court with attorney Galen Bayne-Allison.  Ralph Malcom Uttke appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court calls @ 1:40 pm.  Plea Advisement & Written Waiver of PH. Examination filed.  Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing.  Court accepts waiver and finds probable cause & binds over. Information Filed. Atty Bayne-Allison has copy of information & waives reading & continue to plea & sentencing.  no contest to Ct's 1 & 4 & ct's 2, 3 & 5 dismissed & read in, ct 1 withheld sentence 1 yr probation. AODA & costs, ct 4 20 days jail, c. w/in 60 days, costs, costs from ct 4 be taken out of bond & balance to be returned to poster. 4 days credit, if revoked. Ct 1 Poss of THC, 2nd offense, no contest plea. Ct 4 Bailjumping, no contest plea. No victim rights. Def. admits prior conviction. Stipulate to use complaint for finds of probable cause.  Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Atty Bayne-Allison is satisfied.  Court finds pleas are freely & voluntarily given, and orders Guilty plea on ct 1 Poss of THC 2nd & Bailjumping in ct 4. Ready to proceed with sentencing.  Def. makes statement. Court adopts recommendations & orders Ct's 2 3 & 5 dismissed & read in.
ct 1 withheld sentence 1 yr probation, AODA & follow up treatment & costs
ct 4 20 days jail, 4 days credit, c. 4-9-15 @ 6 pm. costs
Ct 4 Costs to be taken out of bond & balance to be returned to poster.  Atty fees to be paid & if any balance left over to be returned to def. If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered, without further order of the court, against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt. Def. advised of postconviction rights.
